quran[18]{c,v,t}:
  54,23,Thamūd rejected the warnings
  54,24,"They said, “Shall we follow a single human being from among us? Then we would surely be in error and insanity"
  54,25,"Has the revelation been sent down upon him out of all of us? Rather, he is an insolent liar.”"
  54,26,Tomorrow they will know who the insolent liar is
  54,27,"We are sending the she-camel as a test for them, so watch them [O Sālih] and be patient"
  54,28,and tell them that the water is to be shared between them; each should take its drink in turn
  54,29,"But they called their companion, and he undertook the task and hamstrung her"
  54,30,Then how were My punishment and My warnings
  54,31,"We sent against them a single blast, leaving them like trampled hedge-building twigs"
  54,32,We have certainly made the Qur’an easy to understand and remember; is there anyone to take heed
  54,33,The people of Lot rejected the warnings
  54,34,"We sent against them a storm of pebbles, except the family of Lot whom We saved before dawn"
  54,35,as a blessing from Us. Thus do We reward those who give thanks
  54,36,"He had already warned them of Our punishing assault, but they doubted the warnings"
  54,37,"They even demanded that he let them have their way with his angel-guests, so We blinded their eyes, [saying], “Taste My punishment and My warnings!”"
  54,38,By the early morning a lasting torment overtook them
  54,39,Taste My punishment and My warnings
  54,40,We have certainly made the Qur’an easy to understand and remember; is there anyone to take heed